Name: von Willebrand's disease 1
Definition: A von Willebrand's disease characterized by quantitative partial deficiency of circulating VWF that has material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the VWF gene on chromosome 12p13.

Name: von Willebrand's disease 2
Definition: A von Willebrand's disease characterized by qualitative but not quantitative abnormalities of the VWF protein that has material_basis_in mutation in the VWF gene which maps to chromosome 12p13.

Name: von Willebrand's disease 3
Definition: A von Willebrand's disease characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of a severe quantitative defect or virtual absence of VWF in plasma
